<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <head>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p><code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.create">--dynamodb-waiter-create-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code><code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.delete">--dynamodb-waiter-delete-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code><code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.update">--dynamodb-waiter-update-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code> is a global parameter for the <a href="../../../start/tutorials/amazon-dynamodb/home.htm"><MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> DynamoDB extension</a>. It specifies the number of seconds for the <code><a href="https://sdk.amazonaws.com/java/api/latest/software/amazon/awssdk/services/dynamodb/waiters/DynamoDbWaiter.html">DynamoDbWaiter</a></code> to wait before trying to poll your table again (between attempts). This interval is used between calls to verify that the table is <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.create">created and operable</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.delete">deleted</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.update">updated and operable</MadCap:conditionalText>. The default value is <code class="language-text">20</code>.</p>
        <h2>Uses</h2>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="parameter-amazon-dynamodb-waiter-concept.flsnp" />
        <p>The <code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.create">--dynamodb-waiter-create-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code><code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.delete">--dynamodb-waiter-delete-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code><code class="language-text" MadCap:conditions="database-amazon-dynamodb-parameters.update">--dynamodb-waiter-update-fixed-delay-backoff-strategy-duration</code> parameter controls the duration in seconds of the <b>interval</b> between polling attempts:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If your application is <b>more</b> latency-sensitive, set a <b>lower</b> value (shorter interval). This may reduce the amount of time the waiter takes to detect whether your table is in the correct state.</li>
            <li>If your application is <b>less</b> latency-sensitive, set a <b>higher</b> value (longer interval). This may  help you avoid making unnecessary server requests.</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>